{ "controlWidth" : 12, "label" : "TextBlock1", "text" : "

ARIZONA SUPREME COURT

Instructions – Legal Paraprofessional Application

Please read all the following instructions carefully before proceeding. There are several supporting documents listed below which must accompany the online submission. It is recommended that these documents be prepared or obtained prior to beginning the on online application process. For additional assistance, contact the Certification and Licensing Division at LPProgram@courts.az.gov or (602) 452-3378. You may also visit the program website at https://www.azcourts.gov/cld/Legal-Paraprofessional.

  1. Fees: Please refer to Arizona Code of Judicial Administration § 7-210(K) for the applicable NON-REFUNDABLE fee(s) to submit with this application.
  2. Photograph: Upload one color passport-size photograph, two inches by two inches of the head, neck and shoulders only. The photograph must have been taken within the last two years and clearly identify you.
  3. Education: Submit photocopies of all degrees, diplomas, certificates or licenses listed on this application. Submit official transcripts demonstrating coursework where required.
  4. Experience: If required, submit a signed document from a supervising attorney to demonstrate that you meet the experience requirements of ACJA § 7-210(E)(3)(b) and/or (c). Also submit 2 personal and 2 professional references with your application. The following forms may be used in place of formal letters to demonstrate completion of the Experiential Learning and/or Substantive Experience requirements:
    Experiential Learning Attestation Form
    Substantive Learning Attestation Form
  5. Proof of Citizenship/Legal Residency Acceptable Documents: Submit clear, and readable and current (not expired) copies. Refer to the List of Acceptable Residency/Citizenship Documents on the Resource Center page of the Certification and Licensing Portal.
  6. Background Information: If the answer is "Yes" to any question in the Background Section of this application, you are required to submit a SIGNED statement describing in detail all incidents including (1) names of all parties involved, (2) dates and locations, (3) the names and localities of any courts and/or administrative agencies involved, (4) the disposition of each matter, (5) whether the conviction, plea or finding was for a felony, misdemeanor, or no disposition. Copies of court documents, where applicable, should also be included to demonstrate disposition.
  7. Authorization and Release: This form must be signed, notarized and submitted with the application.
